description.narrative:
In Sri Lanka, CEJ advocate people to protect their environmental rights and to conserve nature through various actions. CEJ engages with and provide legal assistance for the marginalized groups, and affected communities through its legal aid programme. By engaging and educating civil society, lawyers, government officers, and mediating environmental disputes, CEJ encourages scientific advocacy and provides advice.
&nbsp;
CEJ aims to enhance environmental/ecological sustainability of the nation, through mediation of environmental conflicts and advocating enforcement of environmental laws and policies. Empowering community and government actors, CEJ envisions - environmental justice for all. 
&nbsp;
The five focus areas &ndash; to improve environmental justice, good governance and ecological democracy; Promote sustainable development and environmental responsible communities; Encourage community participation in decision making on natural resource; Safeguard nature, and eco system and defend frontline communities from human rights violations and campaign, and to Promote environmental sustainability and equity through legal and other means.
&nbsp;
Expected results - Environment justice projected and laws related to natural resources enforced in a righteous manner; Empower environmentally distressed communities through environmental awareness, campaign, research and training; Forest governance is in place and developed to meet the challenge of climate change, and Communities are aware of harmful chemical in food, released environment and in products they use.
&nbsp;
Thematic area Social and economic justice.
